# Wave 1 — Token rewire + in-app UX blockers (design)

**Date:** 2026-04-18
**Branch:** `worktree-ux-wave1-token-rewire`
**Worktree:** `.claude/worktrees/ux-wave1-token-rewire`
**Source audit:** `UX-todo.md` (2026-04-16)
**Canonical tokens:** `/tmp/design-ndrpUZ/socratink-design-system/project/colors_and_type.css`
**Reasoning chain:** praxis:problem-classification → superpowers:brainstorming → (gap-analysis) → writing-plans → gm

---

## 1. Problem framing

The token layer was half-built: primitives and semantic tokens exist in `public/css/variables.css`, but `[data-theme="dark"]` was never defined at `:root` scope. Sixteen component-level override blocks accumulated across `components.css`, `layout.css`, `crystal.css`, `ai-runs-dashboard.css` and three data-loss bugs rode on the gaps:

- BLOCKER #4 — guest concept creation silently discards user input and substitutes a starter map (no error, no warning)
- BLOCKER #17 — analytics concept-select renders invisible in dark mode (cream text on hardcoded near-white bg)
- BLOCKER #24 — mobile viewport hides theme toggle, Save & Sync, Exit Guest via `display: none`; drawer has no footer to restore them, so guest users on mobile have zero egress

Wave 1 fixes the upstream token seam, deletes the downstream overrides that it renders redundant, and repairs three shell/canvas / state-contract bugs that share the same root.

## 2. Scope

### In scope

1. **Token rewire** — expand `public/css/variables.css` to mirror `colors_and_type.css` structure; add `[data-theme="dark"] :root { … }` semantic-token reassignment block; add missing tokens (`--ring`, `--surface-high/highest`, full radii/space/duration/tracking scales, `--node-locked/primed/drilled/solidified`, `--shadow-hero`, `--text-display`, `--page-bloom-*`, `--page-background`).
2. **`:focus-visible`** — add global rule in `base.css` consuming `--accent-ring`.
3. **Analytics state pills** — add `.pill--solid / --primed / --drilled / --locked / --danger` variants in `components.css`; wire analytics-page pill rendering to tile-type.
4. **Dark-override audit** — delete the 11 redundant blocks; keep the 5 genuinely component-specific blocks; move the 65-line token reassignment block from `crystal.css` to `variables.css`.
5. **Mobile drawer footer** — add `.drawer-footer` markup in `public/index.html` containing theme segmented control, Save & Sync, Settings, Exit Guest; render only at ≤480px; reuse existing handlers.
6. **Map-view chrome** — replace `.drawer-toggle` (`<`) and `.map-close-btn` (`×`) inside map view with single `.map-back-link` text control reading "← Dashboard"; `setState({ view: 'dashboard' })` on click. Sidebar stays open at ≥481px regardless of entry vector (mobile ≤480px keeps drawer behavior).
7. **Center-stage creation dialog** — replace sidebar-embedded creation form with a center-stage composition dialog (Notion/Readwise-style reading-room canvas, not "modal form"). Generous max-width, article-paste textarea primary, scrim on shell with `inert` attribute, Tab focus-trap, focus returns to trigger on close, draft preserved in-memory while dialog open.
8. **Guest silent-discard fix** — guest submit disabled behind honest banner ("Guest mode uses sample maps. Sign in to extract your own content."); signed-in failures surface retriable error banner with draft preserved; invariant: failed or unauthorized extraction never calls `concepts.push()`.
9. **Hover tooltip** on remaining drawer-toggle outside map view (UX-todo #26 LOW, cheap resolve).

### Out of scope (deferred)

- Legacy alias sweep (`--bg` → `--surface-page`, etc.) — Wave 2 grep-replace
- `tokens.css` / `components.css` layer extraction — Wave 2 per UX-todo architectural recommendation
- Graph View real Cytoscape render — own track
- 7-screen happy path (threshold / provisional graph / analogical fallback / locked silhouette / repair artifact / interleaving bridge / history) — product work, not UX cleanup
- Anonymous quota-limited real extraction (codex "option 4") — revisit after Wave 1
- Non-BLOCKER UX-todo items (per-route polish, copy drift, stat-tile rebuild) — sweep in later waves

## 3. Decisions

### Q1 — Legacy aliases: **(C) keep w/ DEPRECATED comments, forbid new consumers, Wave 2 sweep**

Rationale: token rewire is already the hardest-to-reverse change in this wave; bundling alias migration on top turns semantic migration into broad app-wide churn with only manual browser verification. (C) preserves delivery momentum, keeps diff reviewable, gives every existing consumer a stable compatibility bridge. Codex council confirmed. Biggest risk flagged: "deprecated" becomes decorative — mitigation is a pre-merge grep check before Wave 2.

### Q2 — Guest silent-discard: **(a)+(c) hybrid + invariant guard**

- Guest mode default: submit disabled with honest banner above form; guest can still browse starter maps
- Signed-in failure: error banner, form populated, no concept created, retry CTA
- **Invariant:** failed or unauthorized extraction never creates a concept. Enforced in `onSubmit` of `startAddConcept` — no `concepts.push` path reachable from 401/403 or `AIService` error.

Rejected pure (b) local fallback generator because it invents a second extraction truth path that looks AI-equivalent to users and directly violates the truthful-state principle (`feedback_product_principles_to_engineering.md`). Codex council confirmed.

### Q3 — Creation dialog: **A-prime — center-stage composition dialog**

Not "modal form" and not "animated panel." Same technical contract as a fixed-position modal dialog, but styled as a quiet composition surface: generous max-width, article-paste textarea primary, scholarly copy, no bounce, `--duration-cozy` / `--ease-standard`, scrim light enough to keep context, hard focus/inert/return-focus, draft preservation on accidental close. Codex flagged biggest risk: becoming a "generic modalized sidebar form." Mitigation is the composition-surface treatment above.

## 4. Token additions (delta from current variables.css)

| Category | New tokens |
|---|---|
| Surfaces | `--surface-high`, `--surface-highest` |
| Backgrounds | `--page-bloom-primary`, `--page-bloom-secondary`, `--page-background` |
| Typography | `--text-display`, full `--tracking-*` + `--leading-*` scales |
| Radii | `--radius-md` (14), `--radius-lg` (20), `--radius-xl` (27), `--radius-2xl` (32), `--radius-pill` |
| Spacing | `--space-0` … `--space-24` (4px rhythm) |
| Motion | `--duration-micro/quick/cozy/ambient`, `--ease-standard` |
| Node states | `--node-locked` (= mauve-200), `--node-primed` (= lavender-500), `--node-drilled` (= #d8a867 warm amber, new), `--node-solidified` (= success) |
| Elevation | `--shadow-hero`, `--shadow-mockup` |
| Pills | `.pill`, `.pill--solid`, `.pill--primed`, `.pill--drilled`, `.pill--locked`, `.pill--danger` variants |
| Dialog | `--overlay-backdrop` (already present), `.creation-dialog` component class (new in components.css) |

`[data-theme="dark"] :root { … }` reassigns the semantic tokens (surfaces, text, accent softs/borders/rings, gradients, shadows, tile, page-background) per `colors_and_type.css` values.

## 5. Override-block audit disposition

| File:Line range | Selector | Action |
|---|---|---|
| `components.css:84-101` (×3) | `.theme-toggle[data-theme="dark"] .theme-toggle-thumb / -icon-sun / -icon-moon` | **Keep** — SVG positioning, not token-derivable |
| `components.css:145-149` | `body[data-theme="dark"] .auth-link` | **Delete** — redundant once `--accent-primary` flips |
| `layout.css:147` | `body[data-theme="dark"] .hero-card` | **Delete** — reassigns `--card-bg` to itself, no-op |
| `layout.css:149-151` | `body[data-theme="dark"] .settings-page-card` | **Delete** — same |
| `layout.css:153` | `body[data-theme="dark"] #card` | **Delete** — same |
| `crystal.css:92-121` (×8) | `.tile-group.empty / .selected / #grid-container::before` | **Keep** — tile geometry hex values beyond tokens |
| `crystal.css:174-238` | token reassignment block | **Move** to `variables.css` |
| `ai-runs-dashboard.css:564-570` (×5) | `.analytics-header / -panel / -status / .metric-card / .tip-card` | **Delete** — redundant once surface tokens flip |

Net: 16 → 5 component-specific kept + 1 moved + 11 deleted.

## 6. Component contracts

### 6.1 `.creation-dialog`

```
.creation-dialog          — fixed overlay, aria-modal="true", role="dialog"
  .creation-dialog-scrim  — backdrop, --overlay-backdrop, click to close
  .creation-dialog-shell  — centered panel, 560px max-width, --radius-2xl,
                            --shadow-hero, inset top highlight for "paper" edge
    .creation-dialog-kicker — "NEW CONCEPT" eyebrow
    .creation-dialog-close — × button
    .creation-dialog-title — "Bring your material." (h3, --tracking-tight)
    .creation-banner       — [optional] guest or error state
    .creation-name-input
    .creation-textarea     — 120px min-height, resize:vertical
    .creation-dialog-meta  — "Your words shape the path; they do not grade you."
    .creation-dialog-actions — Cancel + Extract
```

Lifecycle:
1. Trigger click → create dialog DOM, set `#app-root.inert = true`, append scrim+shell, focus first input
2. Tab trapped via explicit focus-cycle handler (first↔last)
3. Esc or × or scrim-click → close: `removeChild`, `#app-root.inert = false`, return focus to trigger, clear draft
4. Submit → lock form (disable buttons, `aria-busy="true"`), call `onSubmit` from current `buildContentInputUI` path
5. Success → dialog closes, `concepts.push(newConcept)`, `saveConcepts`, `renderGrid`, `selectConcept`
6. Failure → dialog stays open, error banner appears, inputs re-enable with draft intact, no `concepts.push`

### 6.2 `.drawer-footer`

```
.drawer-footer            — visible only at ≤480px, border-top, warm bg
  .drawer-theme-row       — label + segmented control (Light / Dark)
  .drawer-save-btn        — full-width primary "Save & Sync"
  .drawer-footer-split    — flex row, gap 6px
    .drawer-settings-btn  — secondary "Settings"
    .drawer-exit-btn      — secondary "Exit Guest", hidden if signed-in
```

All handlers reuse existing IDs/callbacks (no new JS logic).

### 6.3 `.map-back-link`

```
.map-back-link            — text link, --accent-primary color,
                            8px icon gap, --radius-btn, hover soft bg
```

Click → `setState({ view: 'dashboard' })`. Replaces `.map-view .drawer-toggle` and `.map-view .map-close-btn`. Both selectors are hidden in map view via existing view-class CSS, but the DOM nodes persist — CSS hides them, JS no longer wires clicks.

## 7. Implementation sequence (gm cycles)

Each cycle = one `gm` state-machine run (PLAN → EXECUTE → EMIT → VERIFY → COMPLETE), each its own commit.

| Cycle | Scope | Verify |
|---|---|---|
| **C1** | Token rewire: expand `variables.css`, add `[data-theme="dark"] :root`, `base.css :focus-visible` | Browser: theme toggle, Tab shows ring on every stop light+dark |
| **C2** | Pill variants + analytics wiring | Browser: 4 distinct pill colors on analytics light+dark |
| **C3** | Override audit + deletions + crystal block move | `codesearch [data-theme="dark"]` returns only expected 5 kept blocks + the one moved block in variables.css |
| **C4** | Mobile drawer footer | Browser resize ≤480px: footer visible with 4 actions, each ≥44px tap, theme flip persists on reload |
| **C5** | Map-view chrome + drawer-toggle tooltip | Browser: enter map, top-left is "← Dashboard" text, click returns via setState |
| **C6** | Creation dialog + guest banner + error banner + invariant guard | Browser: guest → banner + disabled; signed-in happy → dialog → extract OK; signed-in simulated 500 → error banner, no concept saved, Tab trapped |

Cross-cycle verify: rerun baseline browser QA prompt from brainstorming chat. All 16 checks pass.

## 8. Success criteria

- All three BLOCKERs resolved (#4, #17, #24)
- UX-todo findings collapsed in Wave 1: #1, #3, #4, #5, #6, #7, #10, #11 (partial), #17, #18, #20, #24, #26 — approximately 13 findings
- `codesearch [data-theme="dark"]` across `public/css/` returns only: `variables.css` (1 block), `crystal.css` (8 tile-geometry blocks), `components.css` (3 theme-toggle SVG blocks). No hits in `layout.css`, `ai-runs-dashboard.css`.
- Focus ring visible via `:focus-visible` on every interactive element light+dark.
- Guest-mode submit path cannot create a concept. Signed-in error path cannot create a concept.
- Center-stage creation dialog passes a11y: `aria-modal`, `role="dialog"`, Tab trap, Esc close, focus return.
- Mobile drawer (≤480px) exposes theme toggle, Save & Sync, Settings, Exit Guest. Each ≥44px tap target.
- Map-view has one back control, reading "← Dashboard".

## 9. Rollback plan

Each cycle is a separate commit. Bad cycle → `git revert <sha>`. Token rewire (C1) is the most entangled; verify in browser before C2 begins consuming new tokens. If C1 must revert, C2–C6 unwind naturally.

## 10. Invariants preserved

- `setState()` remains the sole control-state entry (dialog open/close + map-view back routed through it)
- Knowledge map remains source of truth for drill state (no touches)
- `contentStore` remains volatile by design (no persistence added)
- Gemini SDK shape untouched
- Auth routes untouched
- No new runtime dependencies

## 11. Risks

| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |
|---|---|---|
| C1 token rewire silently regresses a view | HIGH | Per-cycle browser verify light+dark before next cycle starts; each cycle a separate commit |
| Deprecated aliases survive indefinitely | MED | Pre-merge grep check before Wave 2; explicit Wave 2 removal ticket |
| Creation dialog becomes "modalized sidebar" | MED | Composition-surface treatment: generous width, scholarly copy, no bounce, draft preservation |
| Guest invariant guard misses a code path | HIGH | Audit every `concepts.push` call-site; explicit invariant test: simulate 401 + simulate 500 + simulate guest submit, verify `loadConcepts().length` unchanged in all three |
| Focus trap breaks existing drill/tour overlays | MED | Scope focus-trap to `.creation-dialog` only; do not generalize; existing overlays unchanged |

